# Constraints

{% for c in constraints %}
- {{ c }}
{% endfor %}

{% if track_kind == "cli" %}
## CLI-specific constraints

- Errors go to stderr; data goes to stdout.
- Non-zero exit code on failure; document each distinct exit code.
- Every command supports a non-interactive mode (no prompts) so it can be automated in tests.
- Design commands to be scriptable and idempotent where possible.
{% elif track_kind == "desktop" %}
## Desktop-specific constraints

- Respect IPC boundaries between the main process and the renderer/webview.
- The chosen desktop framework (Electron or Tauri) is defined in the track spec; follow its packaging conventions.
- Window/menu structure and lifecycle events are part of the product surface — handle close, minimize, and reopen flows.
{% elif track_kind == "mobile" %}
## Mobile-specific constraints

- Handle platform lifecycle events (foreground, background, deep links, notifications).
- No UI mutations off the main thread; observe the concurrency model of the chosen stack.
- The mobile framework (React Native / Expo or Flutter) is defined in the track spec; follow its navigation and state conventions.
{% elif track_kind == "api" %}
## API-specific constraints

- Implement every endpoint from the API Contract that is in scope for this sprint. Match paths, methods, request schemas, response shapes, and error codes exactly.
- Use a consistent error response schema across all endpoints (e.g. `{"error": {"code": "...", "message": "...", "details": ...}}`).
- Validate all inputs at the boundary — reject bad data early with clear error messages.
- Never expose internal error details (stack traces, database errors, file paths) in API responses.
- Log errors with sufficient context for debugging (request ID, user context, sanitised input summary).
- Handle expected failure cases explicitly (not found, conflict, unauthorized) with appropriate HTTP status codes.
- Write database migrations for all new or modified models.
{% elif track_kind == "worker" %}
## Worker-specific constraints

- Make every job idempotent so retries are safe.
- Use the chosen job queue's primitives for visibility timeouts, dead-letter routing, and back-off.
- Emit structured logs and metrics for every job, including job ID, attempt number, and outcome.
{% endif %}

