# Development Guidelines

- **Always practise test-driven development.** Write tests first, then implement until tests pass.
- **Use the brainstorming skill before adding new components.** Think through module/command/screen design before writing code.
- **Use systematic debugging when tests fail.** Diagnose root causes rather than guessing.
- **Run verification before claiming work is complete.** Ensure all tests pass and the code meets the spec.
{% if api_contract %}- Match the API Contract exactly for all cross-track calls — endpoint paths, request schemas, and response shapes.
{% endif %}- Follow the tech stack and coding conventions specified in the track spec.
- Write meaningful test descriptions that document behavior.
{% if track_kind in ("web", "desktop", "mobile") %}- **Implement error boundaries** at the surface (page / screen / window) level to prevent full-app crashes.
- **Handle all external call failures graciously** — show user-friendly error messages, never raw error objects or stack traces.
- **Every loading state must have a corresponding error state.** If data can be loading, it can also fail.
- **Form inputs must validate and show clear feedback** before submission.
- **Network failures should offer retry options** where appropriate.
{% elif track_kind == "cli" %}- **Handle all external call failures graciously** — emit descriptive stderr messages and set a non-zero exit code; never dump raw tracebacks.
- **Validate inputs at the flag/argument level** with clear error messages.
{% endif %}

